                <note rend="inline" type="source">358.116 M 82/28: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-02T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1921—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:80 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. The Swedish Government has recently assumed an unfriendly attitude toward the
                    missionaries of the Mormon Church in Sweden and has to date ordered the
                    expulsion of 4 of the 11 American missionaries here as was done in 1914. See my
                    number 8, September 17th.<note n="28" xml:id="d190fn28">Not printed.</note> At
                    the instance of Mr. Oscar W. Soderberg, vice president of this church in Sweden,
                    I took the matter up with the Foreign Minister who informed me that the case had
                    been decided in Crown Council meeting and that the attitude of the Government on
                    this point was firm. However, at my request he would allow Mr. Soderberg himself
                    to remain a month to wind up the affairs of the church here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
